      "text": [
        " : \"لاَ بَأْسَ بِأَجْرِ اَلسِّمْسَارِ إِنَّمَا هُوَ يَشْتَرِي لِلنَّاسِ يَوْماً بَعْدَ يَوْمٍ بِشَيْءٍ مُسَمًّى إِنَّمَا هُوَ مِثْلُ اَلْأَجِيرِ \"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.3808 - Al-Hasan ibn Mahbub narrated from Abi Walad, from Abu Abdullah (as), and others from Abu Ja'far Imam Muhammad ibn Ali Al-Baqir (as):\n\"There is no harm in paying a broker's fee. He only buys for people day after day for a specified amount. He is just like a hired worker.\""
        ]
      }
